messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /api/users/auth

- all methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the user routes under the prefix app.use('/api/users', userRoutes);.
- In routes/userRoutes.js the auth endpoint is registered as router.post('/auth', authUser); — this makes the full path /api/users/auth and registers only the POST method for that path.
- The controller comment in controllers/userController.js also documents POST /api/users/auth, and the implementation reads req.body and issues responses, confirming POST is intended.
- No .all, .get, .head, .options, or other method handlers are registered for this route in the code, so only POST is accepted according to the source. (I did not assume Express automatic behaviors like implicit HEAD handling for GET — only explicit handlers in the code were considered.)
